                "permalink_public": "https:\/\/slack-files.com\/T5TCAFTA9-F08JXAYMG3V-cbe357b775",
                "alt_txt": "Now, I don't mean to beat up on poor Google. I actually think they deserve credit for exceptionally good behavior. Many Al companies offer you a way to signal that you don't want your content used for Al, but then they ignore their own signal and if you try to block them they switch IP addresses. I expected Google to say, \"Sure, you can block our Al, we love you, just add the same signal that completely removes your website from our search en-gine.\" But no. They offer a different signal just for Al, and they actually respect it. I added it, and when I checked a few weeks later, Google no longer provided any Al summary at all. So, good on Google for giving creators some con-trol. But I'm skeptical that this is what the future will look like.",
